==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Milk vetch
<hw>Milk" vetch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A leguminous
herb (<spn>Astragalus glycyphyllos</spn>) of Europe and Asia, supposed
to increase the secretion of milk in goats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is sometimes taken for the whole genus
<gen>Astragalus</gen>, of which there are about two hundred species in
North America, and even more elsewhere.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>milkwagon</ent>⟦br⟧
